</ul>
</li>
<li>Stanley R. Parker, <i>Leisure and Work</i>, Allen &amp; Unwin, 1985.</li>
<li>Gilles Pronovost, <i>The Sociology of Leisure. Trend Report</i>, Sage Publications, 1998.</li>
<li>Rhona Rapoport and Robert N. Rapoport, "Four Themes in the Sociology of Leisure," <i>The British Journal of Sociology</i>, vol. 25, no. 2, June 1974, pp.&#160;215–29. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/589313">JSTOR</a></li>
<li>Kenneth Roberts, <i>Leisure in Contemporary Society</i>, CABI, 2006, <a href="Special_BookSources/184593069X" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 1-84593-069-X</a>.</li>
<li>Chris Rojek, "Leisure and Tourism," in Craig J. Calhoun, Chris Rojek, <a href="../Bryan_S._Turner_(sociologist)" title="Bryan S. Turner (sociologist)" class="mw-redirect">Bryan S. Turner</a>, eds., <i>The Sage Handbook of Sociology</i>, SAGE, 2005, <a href="Special_BookSources/0761968210" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-7619-6821-0</a>.</li>
<li>Chris Rojek, <i>Decentring Leisure: Rethinking Leisure Theory</i>, SAGE, 1995, <a href="Special_BookSources/0803988133" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-8039-8813-3</a>.</li>
</ul>
